In support of their theory, the research group’s economists conducted a financial investigation.
In this investigation, three groups have appealed against a partner under different conditions.
The control group reported the actual value of the product concerned and made their point.
In addition to this, they promised that in the event of a win, they would receive another $15 prize.
The third group would have received $15 before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost the money if the auction was lost.
The difference between the two groups consisted in the fact that for one of them, the gain was underlined, and for the other, the loss.
Checking the hypothesis of neurologists the members of the group that played "against loss" were willing to make higher scores of the control group or "winting".
